&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Registered Nurses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 Full time/Part Time Permanent Positions available&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an inspirational leader with a “can do” attitude? who has the knowledge and skills to deliver high quality nursing care&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to take up the post of Registered Nurse on the Colwell Ward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Colwell Ward is a 28 bedded General medical ward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and enthusiastic individual who is able to demonstrate a commitment to patient-centered care and lead the ward forward on our ‘getting to good’ journey. You will need to be an experienced adult nurse with excellent leadership, organisational, interpersonal and communication skills. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be dynamic, proactive and innovative in their approach to work, in order to facilitate excellence in multi-disciplinary working and ensure that patients move efficiently and effectively through the system to enable rapid discharge home. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information and/or an informal visit please contact on Tina Beardmore – Ward Sister (01983) 822099 ext 4303&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
